Getting rid of return true; statement in if (context.getCheckpoint() == StreamCheckpoint.UNINITIALIZED)  block and replacing other returns with return areReadQueuesNonEmpty() should resolve the issue.
In case when we request an address below the trim mark, the second call to discoverAddressSpace(...) will not get called because of:
        if (context.getGlobalPointer() >= maxAddress) {
            return areReadQueuesNonEmpty(context);
        }

